{"amendments":[{"body":"`find_runs_for_bead` is not actually backward-compatible with existing `task-runs.ndjson` history. In the pre-change format, each attempt was persisted as two rows (a `running` start row and a terminal completion row). The new query at `src/adapters/fs.rs:2500`-`src/adapters/fs.rs:2516` only filters by `bead_id` and sorts the raw rows, so a historical attempt is returned twice and can still appear as an in-flight `running` row forever. That breaks the acceptance criterion for answering “what happened to bead X?” from existing milestone state. The query needs to collapse legacy start/completion pairs into a single attempt record before returning results, and there should be a regression test covering a legacy NDJSON file with paired rows.","rationale":"Without legacy-row normalization, the new bead history query overcounts attempts and reports incorrect outcomes on pre-upgrade data, which is a correctness bug in the main feature this change adds."},{"body":"`update_task_run` can fail on legacy data when `run_id` is unavailable, even though `run_id` is explicitly optional. The matching logic in `src/adapters/fs.rs:2387`-`src/adapters/fs.rs:2468` treats every non-terminal row as an open attempt. For pre-change history, completed attempts leave behind their original `running` start rows, so a retry in the same `project_id` can easily produce multiple open matches and trip the new `provide run_id to disambiguate` error path. That means older milestones cannot reliably finalize new attempts unless they happen to have a `run_id`. The updater should recognize and ignore legacy start rows that already have a matching terminal row, or otherwise normalize legacy history before ambiguity checks. Add a test that seeds old-format rows and verifies a no-`run_id` retry can still be finalized.","rationale":"This blocks the new update flow on exactly the backward-compatibility case the task calls out: existing NDJSON data where the new optional fields are absent and retries may still reuse the same `project_id`."}],"summary":"I found two correctness issues, both around backward compatibility with pre-change `task-runs.ndjson` data. The new query/update logic operates on raw rows, but legacy history stores separate start and completion rows per attempt, so `find_runs_for_bead` can double-count attempts and `update_task_run` can become spuriously ambiguous when `run_id` is absent."}